---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Affiliate Disclosure" description="How AI Tools Hub uses affiliate links and how they may affect our content.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-[#171717] mb-6">Affiliate Disclosure</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p class="text-[#666] leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-[#171717]">Last updated:</strong> {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}
      </p>

      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-500/5 my-8">
        <p class="text-amber-200/80 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="text-amber-300">In short:</strong> Some links on AI Tools Hub are affiliate links. If you click an affiliate link and make a purchase, we may earn a commission at no additional cost to you. This helps us keep the site running and continue providing free, honest reviews.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-[#171717] text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Are Affiliate Links?</h2>
      <p class="text-[#666] leading-relaxed">
        Affiliate links are special URLs that track referrals from our site to product websites. When you click one of these links and make a purchase (or sign up for a service), the product company may pay us a small commission.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-[#171717] text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How This Affects You</h2>
      <p class="text-[#666] leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-[#171717]">Nothing changes for you.</strong> The price you pay is the same whether you use our affiliate link or go directly to the product's website. In some cases, our links may even offer you exclusive discounts.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-[#171717] text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How This Affects Our Content</h2>
      <p class="text-[#666] leading-relaxed">
        It doesn't — or at least, it shouldn't, and we work hard to ensure that. Our editorial process is completely separate from our affiliate partnerships:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-[#666] space-y-2">
        <li>We <strong class="text-[#171717]">never accept payment for positive reviews.</strong></li>
        <li>We <strong class="text-[#171717]">never allow companies to preview or approve</strong> our reviews before publication.</li>
        <li>We <strong class="text-[#171717]">clearly mark</strong> all affiliate links on the page.</li>
        <li>We <strong class="text-[#171717]">test every product ourselves</strong> before recommending it.</li>
        <li>We <strong class="text-[#171717]">include honest pros and cons</strong> for every product, regardless of affiliate status.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-[#171717] text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Which Links Are Affiliate Links?</h2>
      <p class="text-[#666] leading-relaxed">
        On review and comparison pages, any "Try [Product]" or "Visit [Product]" button that links externally is likely an affiliate link. We clearly label these sections with a note explaining the affiliate relationship. On pages without affiliate partnerships, all links are regular, non-tracked links.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-[#171717] text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Our Commitment</h2>
      <p class="text-[#666] leading-relaxed">
        We started AI Tools Hub because we were frustrated by unreliable, SEO-churned review sites. Our goal is to be the resource we wished existed — honest, thorough, and developer-focused. Affiliate revenue helps us sustain this work, but it never dictates what we write.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-[#171717] text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Questions?</h2>
      <p class="text-[#666] leading-relaxed">
        If you have any questions about our affiliate practices, please contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@aitools.dev" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">hello@aitools.dev</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
